1
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:18,013
With ten days off,
I figured you'd go abroad.

2
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:20,849
But you're off to Yamagata, right?

3
00:02:20,932 --> 00:02:21,933
Yes.

4
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:23,268
Broke up with your boyfriend?

5
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:27,189
I just prefer the countryside.

6
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:28,815
-See ya!
-Bye!

7
00:02:28,899 --> 00:02:29,983
Let's go to your place!

8
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:31,652
-No way.
-Why?

9
00:02:31,735 --> 00:02:34,529
-Because...
-Later!

10
00:02:34,613 --> 00:02:35,906
Did you get good grades?

11
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:39,117
No, but I don't care.

12
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:40,202
How come?

13
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:43,372
As soon as I get home,
we're traveling to Grandma's.

14
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:45,832
So I won't get yelled at for ages.

15
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,086
Lucky you! Are you going away too?

16
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:51,963
Yeah, to Nagano. How about you, Taeko?

17
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:52,964
I'm not sure.

18
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:55,675
My dad bought a summer home.

19
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,469
Wow... that's great.

20
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:02,307
Such a bad grade in math again.

21
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,894
But I got a "B" in science.

22
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:09,106
Are we going away for the vacation?

23
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,357
Not really.

24
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:13,193
Take me someplace.

25
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:18,448
I'll take you to a movie.
How about "The Crane Lady"?

26
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:21,493
Not that. I mean to the country...

27
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:22,619
The country?

28
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:25,038
Like Grandma's country house.

29
00:03:25,122 --> 00:03:26,623
Grandma lives with us.

30
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:29,126
-Grandpa's then...
-He's dead.

31
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:32,712
We don't have relatives
in the country, so don't ask.

32
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:40,971
<i>My family had lived in Tokyo</i>
<i>for generations.</i>

33
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:44,349
<i>I envied friends who had family</i>
<i>in the countryside.</i>

34
00:03:47,519 --> 00:03:50,480
It's too late to book.
All hotels will be full.

35
00:03:51,106 --> 00:03:52,482
But I really want to go...

36
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:55,444
-What about Onoya?
-Huh?

37
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:59,614
We're regulars. They'd have a room for us.

38
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:00,949
Where's that?

39
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:04,453
Good idea. Taeko's never been there.

40
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:05,746
That's right.

41
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,248
Is it in the mountains? By the sea?

42
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,125
It's in Atami.

43
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:12,919
Atami?

44
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:15,464
You get to ride the bullet train.

45
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:17,549
Sure, you'll love it.

46
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:22,471
Atami...

47
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:25,182
It's great!
Lots of different hot springs...

48
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:28,685
There's the huge Roman Bath.

49
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:34,608
And other little ones, like
the Swan Bath and the Violet Bath.

50
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:36,318
The beautiful Violet Bath!

51
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:38,653
The Violet Bath...

52
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,156
Oh yes. It's fantastic.

53
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:42,991
You love hot springs, right?

54
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:47,454
Since Father's working, you four go.

55
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:48,914
What?

56
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,044
Us?

57
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:55,337
Go too?

58
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:06,139
I'm amazed you show up every morning.

59
00:05:06,223 --> 00:05:08,642
Everyone else has left town.

60
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,230
Aren't you going anywhere?

61
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,190
-Yes, I am.
-Where?

62
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:16,274
Atami.

63
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:19,736
Atami? What's in Atami?

64
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,404
Hot springs.

65
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,160
It's good timing.

66
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:30,831
We're going away next week
to visit relatives.

67
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:34,709
No one will be around for ages.

68
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:39,422
<i>Hello. Okajima residence.</i>

69
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:42,300
Nanako? It's Taeko.

70
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:46,596
I leave today. Any messages for
your husband's family?

71
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:52,143
<i>Not really. Just bring them something.</i>
<i>Maybe cookies.</i>

72
00:05:52,227 --> 00:05:55,313
<i>Say it's from us and I'll pay you back.</i>

73
00:05:55,397 --> 00:05:58,567
Don't worry about it. How's Mom?

74
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:00,068
<i>She's out today.</i>

75
00:06:00,277 --> 00:06:04,239
<i>She was mad you turned down</i>
<i>that guy's proposal.</i>

76
00:06:04,823 --> 00:06:08,577
<i>"At 27, that's the best offer</i>
<i>she's going to get!"</i>

77
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:11,329
It's all she talks about.

78
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:15,333
<i>She's got a point.</i>
<i>You're not young anymore.</i>

79
00:06:15,417 --> 00:06:16,626
Oh, yeah?

80
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,211
<i>Definitely.</i>

81
00:06:18,295 --> 00:06:20,672
<i>You've got to settle down eventually.</i>

82
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:25,302
<i>By the way, did you really work</i>
<i>in the fields last year?</i>

83
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:29,055
Yes, harvesting rice.
This year, I'm picking safflower.

84
00:06:29,139 --> 00:06:30,140
<i>Safflower?</i>

85
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:34,227
Thanks to you, I finally have family
in the countryside.

86
00:06:34,311 --> 00:06:37,731
So, I'm making the most of it!

87
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:40,900
<i>Give me a break!</i>

88
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:44,863
<i>Rather than stay in that old house,</i>

89
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:48,908
<i>why not treat yourself</i>
<i>to a fancy hotel for once?</i>

90
00:06:48,992 --> 00:06:51,036
Maybe you'd meet a nice boy.

91
00:06:51,411 --> 00:06:55,874
No way. You mean a hotel like Onoya?

92
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:57,208
<i>Onoya?</i>

93
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:01,463
<i>Not that again!</i>

94
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,966
<i>You've got to get over it.</i>

95
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:08,136
<i>Let go of that baggage from the past!</i>

96
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:22,317
<i>My sisters, of course, would never go</i>
<i>to a place like Atami.</i>

97
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,363
Grandma...

98
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:29,240
Almost done?

99
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:32,077
Let's go to another bath.

100
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,579
We just went.

101
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,998
Only to the Swan Bath.

102
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:43,755
<i>Bored to tears, I went alone</i>
<i>to the Brothers Grimm Bath,</i>

103
00:07:44,339 --> 00:07:46,758
<i>the Mermaid Bath, the Lemon Bath,</i>

104
00:07:47,342 --> 00:07:50,762
<i>and the Violet Bath, one after the other.</i>

105
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,806
It's enormous!

106
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:56,768
<i>When I got to the Roman Bath,</i>
<i>my head was spinning.</i>

107
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,355
It's amazing...

108
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,158
<i>And I fainted.</i>

109
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:15,662
<i>And with that, my trip was over.</i>

110
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:19,374
<i>Followed by endless weeks of vacation.</i>

111
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,084
<i>Jump on both feet.</i>

112
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:30,927
<i>Now your arms and legs.</i>

113
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:39,144
<i>The other day,</i>
<i>my sisters and I were reminiscing.</i>

114
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:44,024
<i>We couldn't stop laughing</i>

115
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:47,027
<i>as the memories came flooding back.</i>

116
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:53,908
Had one before?

117
00:08:53,992 --> 00:08:55,577
No, it's my first time.

118
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:57,829
I'm the one who asked for it.

119
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,164
Yeah, we know.

120
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:01,041
Where did you buy it?

121
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:03,001
Senbikiya in Ginza.

122
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:04,461
Must have been expensive.

123
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:07,756
How do we eat it?

124
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:09,090
Slice it into rings.

125
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:10,091
But how?

126
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:13,678
I don't know.

127
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:18,099
Didn't you ask in the store?

128
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,523
We'll eat it next Sunday.

129
00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:27,901
Why not now?

130
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,570
We don't know how.

131
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:35,325
I'll have a banana.

132
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:36,993
Me too.

133
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:44,793
Strange fruit they have
in those hot countries.

134
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:49,047
I'm home!

135
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:51,424
I know how to eat the pineapple!

136
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:52,842
Really?

137
00:09:57,722 --> 00:09:58,973
I'll take that.

138
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,184
Mind your fingers.

139
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,144
Wouldn't a carving knife be best?

140
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:18,618
What a nice smell.

141
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,838
It smells so good.

142
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:33,758
I see.

143
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:36,511
Get plates. Quick.

144
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:38,763
Okay.

145
00:10:40,682 --> 00:10:42,767
Let us eat.

146
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,914
It's chewy.

147
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:11,212
Nothing special.

148
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:13,214
Not so sweet.

149
00:11:13,298 --> 00:11:15,341
Nothing like the canned stuff.

150
00:11:15,425 --> 00:11:18,344
Live long enough and you see
lots of different things.

151
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,644
-You can have mine.
-Mine too.

152
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:57,884
It's delicious...

153
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:06,100
Don't force yourself.

154
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:07,226
You'll get a stomachache.

155
00:12:16,694 --> 00:12:19,906
What a letdown.

156
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:24,911
Bananas taste much better.

157
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:26,287
You're so right.

158
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:29,457
Bananas are still the king of fruit.

159
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,708
I'll have one now.

160
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:40,677
<i>If you had to deceive me</i>

161
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:47,266
<i>I wish that you had deceived me</i>

162
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:51,604
<i>Until my death</i>

163
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:55,400
<i>A red-ruby...</i>

164
00:12:55,483 --> 00:13:01,155
The king of fruit is...

165
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:02,991
<i>the banana, after all.</i>

166
00:13:03,074 --> 00:13:05,493
BEST SELLING PRODUCT

167
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:13,126
<i>The year I fainted at the baths</i>
<i>and had my first pineapple...</i>

168
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:18,381
<i>the Beatles came to Japan,</i>
<i>and started the rock 'n' roll band</i>

169
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,967
<i>and electric guitar craze.</i>

170
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:29,392
<i>My sister Nanako, a freshman</i>
<i>in art school, was up on all the trends.</i>

171
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,854
Yeah, the Beatles' lyrics are great.

172
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,981
<i>When she wore a mini-skirt,</i>

173
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:40,278
<i>she'd cover her bottom</i>
<i>going up the stairs.</i>

174
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:48,995
<i>My clever sister, Yaeko, was crazy</i>
<i>about some Takarazuka actress.</i>

175
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,413
Yaeko...

176
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,416
I told you to knock!

177
00:13:57,754 --> 00:14:02,800
<i>My sisters' memories</i>
<i>are mainly of fashion and pop trends.</i>

178
00:14:03,718 --> 00:14:08,473
<i>For them, 1966 is the height of nostalgia.</i>

179
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:12,185
<i>Whereas I was only ten years old.</i>

180
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:17,273
<i>My favorite band had yet to debut...</i>

181
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:22,153
<i>My only memories are the back</i>
<i>and forth between school and home.</i>

182
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,946
Mine was pinned on the wall!

183
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,240
That's nice.

184
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:30,870
And it might be entered
in an essay contest.

185
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,414
The teacher said to take good care of it.

186
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:37,293
-I'd be so happy...
-You didn't finish lunch again.

187
00:14:38,252 --> 00:14:40,588
Why do you hide the pickles
inside the bread?

188
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:42,632
'Cause I hate them.

189
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:46,094
I've got to throw it away. What a waste.

190
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:48,721
Such a picky eater!

191
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:52,058
I'd rather you were a good eater

192
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:55,728
than a good essay writer.

193
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:15,456
How can you drink that horrible stuff?

194
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:21,129
Milk's okay. It's onions I hate.

195
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:24,715
I'm leaving carrots so I've got no choice.

196
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:30,263
Who decided we can only leave one thing?

197
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:31,514
Shall I drink it?

198
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:32,723
Would you?

199
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:36,060
You'll eat my onions next time?

200
00:15:44,694 --> 00:15:45,528
Thank you.

201
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,783
-Carrots?
-We're allowed one thing!

202
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:02,044
Two bowls is gross.

203
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:05,548
People who run in the hall

204
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:10,678
when the hall monitor says stop
should be punished.

205
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:14,390
How are you gonna do that?

206
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:16,184
They shouldn't do it.

207
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:17,477
That's right.

208
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:19,729
You might bump into someone.

209
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:24,108
If I bumped into you I'd bounce a mile!

210
00:16:24,192 --> 00:16:25,234
Get lost!

211
00:16:25,485 --> 00:16:26,402
Oof.

212
00:16:27,278 --> 00:16:29,947
Running is no big deal.

213
00:16:30,031 --> 00:16:30,990
I agree!

214
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:33,034
-Let's change the rule.
-But we already decided.

215
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,619
What's the big deal?

216
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:37,371
Raise your hand if you want to speak.

217
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:39,540
-Here!
-Miss Tani.

218
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:45,546
The hall monitor
should chase the offenders,

219
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:48,090
catch them and punish them.

220
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:49,509
-Me!
-Hey, me!

221
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:50,885
Mr. Suzuki.

222
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:56,098
Then the hall monitor
should also be punished for running.

223
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:57,391
He's right! He's right!

224
00:16:58,059 --> 00:16:59,393
Way to go!

225
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,145
He's right.

226
00:17:01,229 --> 00:17:02,647
Miss Tani.

227
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:07,860
The hall monitor
shouldn't be punished because...

228
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:13,658
it's like a policeman
chasing a speeding car.

229
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:22,083
Any objections?

230
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:26,003
A policeman?

231
00:17:26,087 --> 00:17:27,380
No more running.

232
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:33,302
So, the hall monitor can chase offenders.

233
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,139
Any other issues?

234
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:38,432
Here.

235
00:17:38,516 --> 00:17:39,392
Miss Tani.

236
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,103
-Her again.
-Busybody.

237
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,396
Be quiet.

238
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,898
Some people don't finish lunch.

239
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:50,861
I just read an article on the Vietnam War.

240
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:55,241
There are
many unfortunate people overseas.

241
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:56,742
We're very lucky.

242
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:58,703
Lucky to have you near me!

243
00:18:02,123 --> 00:18:05,209
We should be grateful for our food.

244
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:10,339
We're allowed to leave
one thing on our plates,

245
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:12,216
but I think it's wrong!

246
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:17,430
Goody two-shoes.

247
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:22,685
-It can't hurt to leave one thing.
-Let's all leave milk...

248
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:25,896
-Give it to someone else...
-Of course.

249
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:29,859
-People hide leftovers in bread.
-That's cheating!

250
00:18:30,318 --> 00:18:32,570
-I hate school food.
-Order!

251
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:34,905
If you want to speak, raise your hand!

252
00:18:35,823 --> 00:18:38,326
What a revolting situation.

253
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:45,041
<i>That night in bed,</i>
<i>after chatting to my sisters,</i>

254
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,879
<i>more memories from fifth grade</i>

255
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:53,132
<i>came rushing back.</i>

256
00:18:56,510 --> 00:19:00,890
<i>Our pet dog... School sports day...</i>

257
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:04,310
<i>Being scared by gross horror comics...</i>

